events.name: Denver Nuggets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Jose Alvarado brought fans to their feet repeatedly, and they gleefully sang his name.
headlines.shortLinkText: Alvarado's 38 points pace Pelicans past Nuggets, 121-106

events.name: Phoenix Suns at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Deandre Ayton had 25 points and 10 rebounds and the Phoenix Suns overwhelmed San Antonio 133-95 on Sunday, handing the Spurs their 11th straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Western Conference-leading Suns hand Spurs 11th loss in row

headlines.description: — Even when Jaylen Brown was pouring in the points early, the Boston Celtics knew they'd need to turn to their defense late.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics snap Nets' 4-game winning streak with 103-92 win

headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 21 of his 33 points in the third quarter and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Detroit Pistons 122-112 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ja Morant has 21-point 3rd quarter, Grizzlies beat Pistons

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson scored 23 points and the New York Knicks snapped a five-game home losing streak with a 92-81 win over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks snap 5-game home losing streak in win over Cavaliers

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis dazzled so much, he heard fans chanting “MVP!” And that came while playing on the road.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis scores 55 points, leads Lakers over Wizards 130-119

headlines.description: — Malik Monk scored 20 points off the bench and the Sacramento Kings overcame Zach LaVine's 41 points to beat the Chicago Bulls 110-101 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Monk, Sabonis, Kings overcome LaVine's 41 points, beat Bulls

events.name: Indiana Pacers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Jerami Grant scored 28 points to lead the Portland Trail Blazers over the Indiana Pacers 116-100 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trail Blazers beat Pacers in Lillard's return from injury
